http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/A-hectic-day-for-Owaisi/article14023392.ece

All India Majlis-e-Ittehadul Muslimeen floor leader Akbaruddin Owaisi on Wednesday conducted a road show at the Jangammet ward in the Chandrayangutta assembly constituency.He spent close to six hours campaigning in the ward where around 27 other candidates belonging to different political parties and also Independent candidates are in fray.Mr. Owaisi was accompanied by Jangammet ward Majlis candidate Abdul Rahman.As the cavalcade traversed through the labyrinthine lanes of Gazi-e-Millat Colony, G.M. Chowni and Jangammet areas, men made a beeline on the road to meet the leader, while women preferred to watch the going-ons from the terrace.Mr. Owaisi promised to develop the area and assured to provide more civic amenities to the residents in the localities. Elaborate security arrangements were made during his visit.